    "body": "It would be handy if $spack worked in environment's spack.yaml file, as it does in `config.yaml`.\r\n\r\n### Rationale\r\n\r\nI'd like to be able to refer to the root of the spack installation when describing the root of a view in an environment's `spack.yaml`.\r\n\r\nCurrent choices seem to absolute paths and relative paths (which seem to be relative the the cwd when `spack install` is run.\r\n\r\nWhen I tried using `$spack/foo` I ended up with a view rooted at the literal `$spack/foo`.\r\n\r\n### General information\r\n\r\n- [x] I have run `spack --version` and reported the version of Spack\r\n   - `0.14.1-684-f912cce7e`\r\n- [x] I have searched the issues of this repo and believe this is not a duplicate",
    "performed_via_github_app": null
